        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1896983691" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9027093076901547259"><b>4.5 Stars. Another winner for Chevy Stevens!</b><p>Andrew is a creepy-scary dude who believes his wife Lindsey is a possession to be controlled. He is obsessively jealous to the point of ridiculous and when he begins to drink, oh boy, he becomes cruel and violent.....except to daughter Sophie.</p><p>
  <b>&quot;Your dad loved to scare me.&quot;</b>
</p><p>Chevy Stevens&apos; story of a marriage gone bad is <b>NOT</b> like so many others I&apos;ve read with a similar theme, but has more than one mysterious and thrilling spin that takes the reader in </p></span>
  <span id="freeText9027093076901547259" style="display:none"><b>4.5 Stars. Another winner for Chevy Stevens!</b><p>Andrew is a creepy-scary dude who believes his wife Lindsey is a possession to be controlled. He is obsessively jealous to the point of ridiculous and when he begins to drink, oh boy, he becomes cruel and violent.....except to daughter Sophie.</p><p>
  <b>"Your dad loved to scare me."</b>
</p><p>Chevy Stevens' story of a marriage gone bad is <b>NOT</b> like so many others I've read with a similar theme, but has more than one mysterious and thrilling spin that takes the reader in various directions that certainly kept me guessing throughout the story. Even when I was sure I knew the outcome of the story, I was thrown yet another curveball leading me elsewhere.</p><p>I've read and enjoyed several Stevens' novels, and except for the <i>mild</i> animal cruelty, <b>NEVER LET YOU GO</b> is now a new favorite.</p><p>Many thanks to NetGalley and St. Martin's Press for the ARC in exchange for an unbiased review.</p></span>
